########################################################################################################################
#Pycharm
########################################################################################################################
##################
#Shortcuts
##################
#General:
    # Hide Execution window = Shift + EC 
    # Settings = Alt + Ctrl + S  
    # Comment/Uncomment = Ctrol + / (Division Numpad)
    # Hide Code Folding = Settings - Fold -  disable show code folding outline
    # Switch Tabs: Alt + Right/Left Key
    # Close current Tab: CTRL + F4 --> change to ctrl + w
    
#Interpreter
    - Unten rechts --> Python Interpreter verwendet/wechseln

#Keybinding:
    - File - Settings - Keymap
        - Top left dropdown --> current running version (can download different in "Plugins"
        - Reset/Delete/Change between Keymapsettings in dropdown 
        - Set new shortcuts for example: run... --> F5 --> creates new element in dropdown
        
-Marking:
    - shift + up/down = mark whole lines
    - double control + hold control + up/down = edit line at this point
    
-Search:
    - Search for Files
        - SHIFT SHIFT
        - CTRL + Shift + N
    - Path of current File:
        - Hover over File Tab
        - Crosshair Symbol oberhalb Projektexplorer, Ã¶ffnet aktuellen Dateipfad
        - Rechts daneben: Collapse all
        
-Running Files:
    - Button greyed out: Rightclick Tab/File -> run once
    - Run File:
        - default: alt + shift + f10
        - custom keymap: F5

################
#Packages
################
#Install:
    - Settings -> Project:Github --> Python interpreter
    - hover over -> tooltip menu --> install Package 
    - unten in "Terminal" Tab wechseln --> pip install package
    - Warning lightling pupl when importing missing package

